item.title: 771. Jewels and Stones
item.author: Author
item.description: Description You’re given strings jewels representing the types of stones that are jewels, and stones representing the stones you have. Each character in stones is a type of stone you have. You want to know how many of the stones you have are also jewels. Letters are case sensitive, so “a” is considered a different type of stone from “A”. Test cases Example 1 Input: jewels = "aA", stones = "aAAbbbb" Output: 3 Example 2
